  4. The last workflow trigger (third run) failed to start (server-side issue) so I could not verify the fixes with a successful run.

Concrete next-code changes required to fix remaining issues (apply and then run)
Below are the exact, minimal, mechanical fixes that will resolve the bulk of remaining compilation errors. I cannot run them again because I've exhausted the run attempts, but apply these changes and run the workflow to verify.

1) Update processors to use ArrayNode instead of ArrayList when calling EntityService.getItems

Example change (MatchingProcessor — simplify to use ArrayNode):
- Replace code like:
  CompletableFuture<java.util.ArrayList<com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode>> fut = entityService.getItems(Subscriber.ENTITY_NAME, String.valueOf(Subscriber.ENTITY_VERSION));
  java.util.ArrayList<JsonNode> items = fut.get();
  if (items != null) {
      for (JsonNode node : items) { ... }
  }
- With:
  CompletableFuture<com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ArrayNode> fut = entityService.getItems(Subscriber.ENTITY_NAME, String.valueOf(Subscriber.ENTITY_VERSION));
  com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ArrayNode items = fut.get();
  if (items != null) {
      for (JsonNode node : items) { ... }
  }

Make the same pattern change in:
- MatchingProcessor
- PersistLaureateProcessor
- DedupAndVersionProcessor
- Any other class that expects a CompletableFuture<java.util.ArrayList<JsonNode>> from entityService.getItems(...)

