4) Convert ArrayNode (jackson) to collection or map values properly when code needs java.util.List
- If the processor needs a List<JsonNode>, convert explicitly:
  com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ArrayNode arr = ...;
  List<JsonNode> items = new ArrayList<>();
  if (arr != null) { arr.forEach(items::add); }
  // or iterate arr directly

5) Fix any usages of technicalId versus laureateId naming conventions
- Some code expects the persisted object's technicalId to exist in the JSON as "technicalId" or "laureateId". Ensure the code that extracts UUIDs uses the correct field name that the entity will persist. Consistency between entity fields and processors is necessary.

